NAME
       fork - create a child process

SYNOPSIS
       #include <unistd.h>

       pid_t fork(void);

DESCRIPTION
       Duplicates the calling task. The child receives a copy of every
       page table entry, of every open file descriptor, and a copy of
       the user stack at the syscall entry point. Both processes
       continue execution from the same instruction. The child sees a
       return value of 0; the parent sees the child PID.

       Cervus does not implement copy-on-write yet; the child page map
       is fully populated at fork time.

RETURN VALUE
       0 in the child, the child PID in the parent, -1 on failure.

ERRORS
       ENOMEM     not enough memory to copy the page map
       EAGAIN     pid table exhausted

SEE ALSO
       wait(2), execve(2), exit(2)
